{
  "text": "According to a previous study evaluating the differences between components of pain after surgery, [CITATION_1] a sample size of 20 patients per group was used. The primary goal of this study was to evaluate the characteristics of postoperative pain during the first 24 hours after RCNP in the control group. The secondary goal was to compare the superficial incisional pain score between the 2 groups at each time point.",
  "citation_candidates": [
